g.text: Since 2007 epidemiologist have been tracking the rate at which honeybee colonies fail in the united States. There are an estimated 2.81 million managed honey producing colonies as of 2020. Keeping track of how many active honey producing hives there are each year allow for bee keepers and farmers to gauge how their communities are being impacted. With this information it is possible to predict how crops will be effected by lower pollination levels by bees.
Honey Bee Colony Losses in the united States
